Wiper leader Kalonzo Musyoka has said he will run for President in 2022.&ldquo;Wiper will be in government and we will work hard for this great nation,&rdquo; he said on Saturday.Kalonzo (pictured) spoke during a fundraising for Machakos governor hopeful Wavinya Ndeti.He said he can propel the nation to excellence.Former Deputy Speaker and Garissa Township MP aspirant Farah Maalim promised to support Kalonzo&rsquo;s election bid and praised him for his leadership skills.&ldquo;All indications show we are winning the Garissa Township seat. But my campaign will actuallystart after August 8 for Kalonzo,&rdquo; he said.Maalim and Kalonzo pledged to support Ndeti&rsquo;s bid to unseat Machakos Governor Alfred Mutua.&ldquo;This is a fight I enjoy engaging in. The people of Machakos should not be afraid because we will fight and ensure that Wavinya is on the ballot. The battle has been clearly drawn and I am ready for it,&rdquo; Kalonzo said.Ndeti promised to provide clean water, quality healthcare, improved education and uplift youths and women if elected.&ldquo;This battle is not for the people of Machakos, but mine. I will soon launch my manifesto,&rdquo; she said.Recently, Ukambani leaders endorsed Kalonzo as NASA presidential candidate Raila Odinga&rsquo;s running mate.Raila and Kalonzo will fight it out with President Uhuru Kenyatta and Deputy President Willam Ruto&rsquo;s Jubilee Party.Ndeti got a temporary reprieve after the High Court directed the IEBC to include her name in their Gazette notice.Justice George Odunga last Friday temporarily set aside a ruling by the IEBC disputes tribunal that nullified her Wiper nomination.